  "texts": [
    "have demonstrated ultra-low switching energy in MoS 2 -based memtransistors comparable to h-BN-based memristors, attributed to the high grain boundary density and small grain size within the as-grown MoS 2 layer, facilitating the migration of sulfur vacancies and reducing energy consumption [86].",
    "In addition to programming energy, the consideration of read energy or compute energy is also crucial as it plays a significant role in synapse inference.",
    "The overall energy consumption within an array is determined by the collective read energy of individual devices within the array.",
    "Despite its significance, information regarding specific read energy values is limited in the existing literature.",
    "Therefore, there is a pressing need to focus research efforts on accurately measuring read energy in order to facilitate the optimization of energy consumption during synapse inference."
  ]
